label: alternative form
description: In definitions: An "alternative form" of a given word is another spelling of that word which is pronounced differently: for example, _killikinick_ is an alternative form of _kinnikinnick_. (A spelling which is pronounced the same is an "alternative spelling": for example, _judgement_ is an alternative spelling of _judgment_.) / As a header: The header "Alternative forms" [encompasses](https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/Wiktionary:Entry_layout#Alternative_forms) both alternative spellings (_judgement_, _judgment_; _sulphur_, _sulfur_) and alternative forms (_killikinick_, _kinnikinnick_), as well as differences in hyphenation (_tea-cup_, _teacup_), capitalization (_LASER_, _laser_), and other similar differences (_naïveté_, _naiveté_).

label: idem, gelijk woord of gelijke uitdrukking
formal
description: Language used in formal or official contexts.

label: informal
description: Language used in informal or everyday contexts.

label: slang
description: Informal language use within a limited environment or a specific group.

label: legal
description: Language used in legal literature and in the judiciary.

label: archaic
description: Words or meanings that are no longer in active use and which speakers may have trouble understanding.

label: derogatory
description: Words or idioms intended to ridicule or hang out the person or thing it denotes.

label: figurative
description: Words which, in addition to their original meaning, are used in a transferred or metaphorical meaning.

label: simile
description: A figure of speech where one thing is compared to another using "as" or "like".

label: euphemism
description: A mild or indirect word or expression substituted for one considered to be too harsh or blunt.
